<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="265" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00 Congress, Communist International,
                            VII/91: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-28T19:00:00-04:00">August 28,
                                    1935—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>206. Press reports from Moscow state that in connection with the recent
                            Congress of the Communist International oral protests have been made to
                            the Soviet Government by Italian and Latvian representatives there.
                            Please consult them promptly and report facts fully by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>